                    <span class="title">
                        Daly Slides Into New Seat for Dirt Track Debut </span>
                </span>
                <span class="nav-item__details">
                    The United States Auto Club (USAC) announced Monday that Daly will pilot a second entry for Landon Simon Racing in the Driven2SaveLives BC39 presented by NOS Energy Drink on Thursday at The Dirt Track at IMS. He’ll make his USAC P1 Insurance National Midget debut on the quarter-mile clay oval specially constructed inside Turn 3 of the famous 2.5-mile superspeedway.
